content.description:
Start just right of Dumpster Diving. Sit start using underclings for both right and left hands. Make a tuff move to a right sidepull. Figure out how to get onto the slab. Top it out. 

  The right arete is most definitely off.
From a sit on the right, follow the arête/ sloper feature left through thin holds to the end of the feature and top out.
content.location: On smaller Boulder just south of Dumpster Boulder.  The problem faces south.

content.description: The face directly to the right of Rhoads Rage.  Some holds may have broken off of the face as a dead rotten tree was leaning up against it when the problem was first found.
Rhoad Rage is the obvious arete on the Southwest corner of the boulder.  Great warmup.
Start as for Dumpster Diving with underclings sitting.  Climb straight up the arête not moving left to the big shelf.  Good fun.
Little Fingers is on the East side of the boulder.  Start on the ledge and go up on big holds.
content.protection: A pad or two and spotter maybe.

content.description: A nice little small one.. B side.   Start matched on the arete, gain juggy ledges then get to the top.  Kinda cool. The start is the crux.
content.protection: 2 pads, fold one to level the landing.
content.location: 30/40 feet above the Dumpster Boulder.  Uphill side of boulder.

content.description: Start on great crimper jugs and thin feet in the middle of the face. Head straight up. Feet and hands near the left arete are off. If you're tall, you can reach for the top in one move after getting feet up high. Others will use a small intermediate crimper.
content.location: North face of boulder, between Dumpster Diving and Little Fingers.

content.description: Dumpster Diving sits on the northwest corner of the boulder.  Start on the right side of a small alcove on two sidepulls and move up through a gaston and a sloper.  Finish out left on the big ledge.
content.protection: It has a pretty nice landing.  A pad or two would work fine.

content.description: Physical and full body feature climbing.. Start left hand gaston pinch, and right lower, opening the elevator door on a fin.  Gain the arete and continue up.  A slopey crimp in the face and a knee scum or two could be helpful.
content.location: 100 feet straight up from dumpster diving in the talus.

content.description: Climb left arete of nice clean boulder.
content.location: This boulder sits about 200ft up and right of the Stache/Dogwalk boulder, and faces downhill.  Really obvious once you see it.

content.description: The Dumpster boulder is a nice little boulder that sits about 20 yards northwest of the Half Dome Boulder.  The problems are all fairly moderate and it's a great little spot to warmup for the day.  Plus it's always fun to climb on a freestanding boulder!
